CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 29, 1961, pg. 9 reads: "Miss GPIL" Contestants - These lovely young ladies, who are competing for the title of "Miss GPIL" will be introduced at a frappe sip July 30, at the home of Nellye Baron, a member of the sponsoring group, the Original D.I. Club, at 1253 Grotto St. Left to right, front row: Cheryl Davis, Charlotte Whitelow and Beverly White.  Second row: Pherbie Scott, Dorothy May and Elexis Moore.  Third row: Olivia Diggs, Mrs. Helen Smalley, sponsor, and Lenora Yates. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of woman and eight young women competing for title of "Miss GPIL" standing on steps of brick building, including first row: Cheryl Davis, Charlotte Whitelow and Beverly White; second row: Pherbie Scott, Dorothy May and Elexis Moore; third row: Olivia Diggs, sponsor Helen Smalley, and Lenora Yates
